reviews.text: Expensive. It's worth seeing the pagent once. Great show. Always sells out. St least theme is different every year

A bucket list MUST see!  Words do not do justice to try and describe this incredible and amazing transformation of art. 

This was my third visit and the theme, under the sun, was my favorite.  They added a lot of fun interactive and playful elements that kept the audience engaged.
Pros: Stunning, amazing and utterly unforgetable show.  Food and drinks readily available.  Art show on premise so a lot to see.  Great narrator where patrons get a lesson in the art pieces as they hear the facts and scenarios behind the paintings.  Usually very entertaining.
Cons: Good tickets can be hard to come by.  Seats in the back MUST use binoculars to see what is going on.
Show starts at 8:30p as it must be dark and it ends well after 10:30p.  After a great dinner, a glass of wine, eyelids start to get heavy near the end of the show.

The pageant of the masters never disappoints. I don't have the opportunity to go too often, but this is the fourth time I have been. The artistic displays are phenomenal; an experience hard to put into words. This year's artists in the festival represent some very eclectic styles.

Unbelievable! I have been wanting to attend for so long,  and finally made a road trip to Laguna Nigel with some friends.  We were spellbound by the magic of the technique, particularly the lighting.
This year marked the centennial for the Laguna Arts group, so a great deal of the show highlighted local art culture and history- what a treat! So wholly enjoyable for this newbie to the art scene.  My friends loved the show, as well, and we all agreed that we would be back with others...must share the experience and see what will come next!
Laguna Nigel is an exciting and inviting artist's community, and the galleries were plentiful.
We were quite happy with our location around the corner at the Residence Inn in San Juan Capistrano, and the girls took in the mission while there.
You have to see it to believe it. Art comes to life.

Quaint little place with a beautiful succulent garden around the patio seating. We we're greeted by an owner with, "Welcome Home" 
 Husband got a seafood burrito and loved it. I had the chicken nachos and while they were good it had a taste of fish which was odd to me 😂

Excellent food. Good prices . Small restaurant... but they make you feel at home. Definally will tell my friends to stop by when they are in laguna Beach. This place is a must stop. The real Mexican food.
Wow.  Don't miss this place.  Mexican breakfast to die for!  Huevos rancheros were perfect.  Legit breakfast burrito.  Stop and see!  Look at my pics.
Nice long time local restaurant with good Mexican food
Love the food and the people who work there! The atmosphere couldn't be more authentic I always run into my neighbor's and friends 😋

This place charges a fee for you to go pee. Yes they charge you to use the bathroom!?! Fun outing for us last weekend. Imagine going here & wanting to eat with your family & being excited for pizza. Then you roll in and you want to use the bathroom because you were at the beach all day & you have to put 25 cents in to use the bathroom? Oh heck no. And your not from around here so you don’t really know what to do?!? I don’t carry around quarters. We left!! We went to this cute little car restaurant down the road instead and I could use a  bathroom without paying a fee for peeing. I could actually walk into the bathroom without putting money into a slot machine to go pee.
The huge individual slice is ginormous! Decent quality and value.
Always loved Gina's pizza. The best
Love the pizza from here, excellent ingredients, great service
Vegan cheese. Close to a park. Food is pretty  good.
Believe the hype. Pretty great breakfast spot in Laguna Beach without the Laguna Beach price tag. It gets busy but outside seating is nice, you can see the ocean...kinda.

So I just took a dive and we were looking for a place to grab some breakfast. It had been a long time seeing her from Australia and without her knowing this area... I trusted her.
 
Welp, she was right! I got the lox bagel but looking over the menu in general made me really appreciate the quality and price.

The place was stacked with people and I'll be headed here again with my other dive partners!

UNBELIEVABLE!! Maybe the best breakfast-lunch experience ever!  Not one bad thing to say about my family's recent dining experience.  You know a place is great when all five people in your party rave about the experience.  I strongly suggest this place.  Although it was my first time, other members in the party have eaten at this place several times.  My veggie (feta and spinach) omelet was outstanding.  The seasoned potato cubes and toast were also excellent.  However, the  star of the plate was the homemade raspberry jam.  I think it was something more of a jam on steroids.  That stuff is addicting.  Service is outstanding and price to portion is good considering the quality of food.  My omelet was at least three eggs...large eggs (maybe even four).  You get a handful of potatoes, two pieces of toast, and the jam for $11.50. Throw in the quaint inside and outside deck within view of the ocean a mere couple of blocks away and you can see why this place is a gem.  I urge you to check the menu (pictures of various items) on their website.  It's pretty big with tons of variety.
Wonderful place.  I had an amazing omelet and fresh butterscotch flavored coffee.  Fresh and fast and one of those places you look forward to returning and trying other new things.
One of the best breakfast & lunch spots in Laguna Beach. I highly recommend the sliders & the turkey club.
Top class. Excellent daily rotating craft beer board. Beautiful Mexican dishes freshly cooked. Relaxed atmosphere and good friendly staff. My new local!

For what it is, it's a great place to eat. I appreciate the fact the beef nachos were made with actual (I assume) brisket-style beef instead of cheap mince. Self-serve salsa/garnish station. Wide selection of beers on-tap, covers the whole front wall basically. Non-alcoholic drinks (including water) are self-serve at a dispenser machine though, so don't expect a complete table service experience. We initially were confused as to where to find drinks as the machine is relatively hidden in one corner.
This was a recommendation from the folks at Catch Surf.  It was excellent.  I had the grilled fish burrito.  The beer list is also very good
Great fresh and quick Mexican food with a good beer selection. There are plenty of vegetarian and seafood options, and a solid salsa bar. This is a great lunch option near Treasure Island Beach.
Loved this place. Amazing staff. Beard guy (didn't catch your name) and Jeff are the best. Amazing food and bar vibe.

At the risk of revealing a best-kept secret, I am putting in a plug for one of my top faves in Laguna. This is the place the locals eat. The food is great and reasonably priced.

The other reviews below do a great job of describing it and I would add that there is a free parking lot in the back if you are early/brave/lucky. It has at least a dozen spaces and despite their request for local construction workers to not park there, is usually filled with pickup trucks.

The burgers are on par with your best burgers anywhere. The breakfasts are dependable and tasty. The atmosphere is old Laguna. Check egos at the door and don't forget to tip the hard-working wait-people.

Remember, this is breakfast and lunch only, closing by early afternoon. Weekends, you can expect a wait.

(Originally posted to Yelp 02–19-2011)

Went in for breakfast, got some french toast and eggs and it was all just... Ok. Okay service (the waitress seemed grumpy) and the okay food, truthfully it was kind of bland but their hot sauce was great. Good for a quick breakfast, but wasn't memorable. But they're pretty dog friendly which is a plus!

Very small place and not a lot of room or seating. I came about 1030am on Saturday and managed to find a couple open seats. French toast and bacon were excellent. Probably could have made the potatoes more crispy but still very good. Good coffee and service I don't think there is a rest room
Quaint place with friendly and helpful server. Good pancakes.
I had a great breakfast served up quickly and hot by friendly servers. The historic place had a great vibe from a crowd of regulars.
The place is friendly and cozy and the staff is very nice. I went just once, but loved it. The "stand up man" was brilliant too. Absolutely worth visiting for a pleasant evening.

Lived in Woodlands for around 15 years and have been so lucky to have this on my door step. I'm a semi regular and can thoroughly recommend it for a good night out. £3 Tuesday's are always good for a laugh, can be a bit hit and miss but if seen some belters at it over the years!
Just been there for the first time and have no words. Cozy space and good comedians. If you haven't been already you need to give it a go. I'll be back soon

Funky basement comedy venue. Excellent staff service and brilliant entertainment. Word of warning get there early if you want a table, late comers will find themselves on bar stools or standing if it's a busy night.

If I could give it less I would. Far too busy. Party of 4 paid £50 to stand for 2hrs then get told off by some jobsworth(who was lucky not to be put on his arse for his attitude) for daughter whispering that her back was sore from standing. Check out Rotunda instead. Nice atmosphere, nice staff and have given up on The Stand now.

Edit: Complained about experience to customer services.  Was told a complete pack of nonsense which didn't reflect our experience at all.  Advise me that we had been offered seating when we arrived, we weren't. Advised me we had to be spoken to in the first half of the show, we weren't.  Back-covering when staff are clearly in the wrong and need a lesson in manners as well as customer service.  I'm fairly accomodating and realise things can go wrong or people can have off nights, but the incident and the followup conversations were woefully inadequate and reinforce my feeling that The Stand is dead as a comedy option for my friends, family and myself.  The Rotunda is a much better prospect with good seating, quick table service, good acts, plenty space.  The Stand has done just that, stood still for 30 years.  Move on, get better and for the love of god start treating paying customers with a bit of damn respect.

I love it here. Not as pretentious as many popular Laguna spots. It's got a wonderful rooftop patio with a great view of main beach. The food has never let us down, the drinks are great. The prices a touch high and the service is just okay...but I absolutely love going and sitting outside. You cant go wrong with the breakfast menu, but I also highly recommend the salmon/rice.

Wasn’t the best experience. They have a sign that explains about happy hour at lunch but when you get in, there is nothing. We ordered burger which came with sourdough and was really stiff. The smoothie has more water inside. We came to eat crepes but at 2pm they were already out of them

Excellent food, lovely location with beach view both from inside and patio. Friendly and efficient service. Reasonable prices, good portions. Excellent omelette, pancakes, Monte Cristo, and tasty fresh bread. On Sundays, they offer a free mimosa with brunch items. The only downside is finding parking. Will definitely return.

The view was awesome! I enjoyed sipping on a latte on the balcony while waiting for our food. The espresso is Lavazza which was very good! They also had milk alternatives. The milk froth was not spectacular but it was acceptable. 

As far the food goes it was alright. Nothing out of this world but not bad. We both had omelettes. The bakery items looked great but we were too full to try them. 

What is worth raving about is the service! We went in at around 11am on a Wednesday and were served right away. Our server was Justin. He was super friendly and made us feel like a local. 

We would go back for the views and the great service.

The view from the upstairs terrace here is magnificent. If you're looking for a nice place to have lunch and see the ocean on a pretty day, it's hard to beat. My seafood quiche wasn't quite as spectacular as the veiw. The crust was overcooked and tough, and the filling, although pretty good, wasn't particularly flavorful. The salad that came with it was very nice, but quite dry, to the point where I needed to request extra dressing. It's hard for me to say how much of this was due to the particular day that I went there vs how much is just the way the restaurant chefs prepare the food. I would definitely give this place another go!

Fantastic rooms, great views. Hotel service was slow and food in the restaurant wasn't as good as I'd hoped. In fairness, the staff were very nice and helpful but because of the hotel's layout, getting to the rooms isn't fast or easy.

Excellent choice, the hotel is amazing, something truly different. You can get a private pool right on your room with an amazing view, the jeep ride to get in and out of the hotel is something nice too. Definitely staying here again.

visited hundreds of hotels during my private and business time in over 115 countries, lot of beaches but I have to say this hotel is in my TOP5. Private pool in 2floor room, super clean, hidden from people, private balcony with best view on Acapulco bay, window for food and drinks for keeping your privacy and extraordinary service. Food was excellent. I literally spend two full days just in room enjoying privacy, view and my spacious pool and private terrace. Will return no doubt! :)

Very interesting concept, some flows in it tho. I love the idea of privacy (had a room with private pool). Stayed Wednesday through Sunday.  Unfortunately, on Friday-Saturday the place got crowded. Loud noises, different music playing from  four different places, loud laughter, kids screaming, etc. 
They say Breakfast included, but in fact it's a pot of coffee ans two small pastries, all other food you have to order/ go to one of the restaurants. Speaking of ordering - room service is extremely quick and professional. 
Beach Club is nice - salt water pool is so much fun. Fish ans sea stars are everywhere!
Sunset Bar is another cool place - you can enjoy the sunset from the top of the mountain having a drink.
Overall, I'd say i enjoyed my stay there.

Aging property with beautiful views. The rooms are definitely dated but not a huge deal to me. The beach club is a highlight but the shuttle to get to and from the beach club takes way too long. It's about a 10 minute ride from the beach club to the hotel but we'd wait sometimes 45 minutes for a ride.
Nice menu....good variety. Waitress was very friendly. Only complaint was that they ran out of the prime rib sandwich special...when we got there they only had two left.
It was delicious ! The view is not bad either.
Loved it, I'm sad it closed

Excellent food, thoughtfully and imaginatively prepared, using first rate fresh ingredients.  Warm and pleasant atmosphere with friendly professional service.  If its not fresh they won't serve it.  You can even order the fish on Monday.

This was an absolutely gorgeous restaurant at the Montage that also offered amazing food. The wine list was extremely extensive and the cocktail menu was good. If you enjoy beer their selection was a little limited. The food was portioned for several courses and all of it was innovative and creative. The restaurant was beautifully decorated and had great views of the ocean and surrounding area. I would definitely recommend this place to anybody looking for an elevated dining experience in the Laguna area.
Best birthday dinner I've had in years.  Pricey tho, be prepared.
Great food. Staff was friendly and attentive. Georgia was awesome.

The Stafford studio exceeded my expectations when my wife and I had our anniversary dinner we stayed on property concierge is awesome and the chef style this out everything was to the utmost perfection we did order almost everything off the appetizer menu just start thank you very much for the staff and to the chef
